isting tests are written in Kotlin. While this isn't directly categorized as a setup issue, agent_guidance could suggest to \\\"keep tests in Kotlin and define data classes,\\\" even if that's not formal setup advice.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"hoplite-core is self-contained for meaningful core coverage: the resolved artifact only needs its normal transitive Kotlin dependencies, and core APIs can be exercised with MapPropertySource, built-in .properties/.props parsing, decoders, preprocessors, and resource/classpath loading without Docker or external services.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. For core-only tests, prefer MapPropertySource or built-in .properties/.props resources. Avoid YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON examples unless intentionally adding the corresponding optional Hoplite format module, since those parsers are not part of hoplite-core.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The README's most common getting-started examples use YAML and mention optional format modules; generated tests copied from those examples would fail with hoplite-core alone unless rewritten to use MapPropertySource or .properties/.props.\",\n    \"Version 3.0.0 changes environment variable property-source behavior, but exercising that path is optional and not required before meaningful reachability coverage is reachable.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02f02fd9ad2d3e62016a3f24fcf0b08194a05ffbc78fcddb02\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 802, "output": 758, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34328, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782523124009, "responseId": "resp_02f02fd9ad2d3e62016a3f24f492d48194b2d9918a3ea1ff5c"}}
